cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning image segmentation framework that is robust to missing imaging modalities. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The approach involves learning an embedding of the input image into a single latent vector space for each modality, which can be further processed to yield the desired segmentation. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the approach on two neurological MRI datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image segmentation, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
